&lt;p&gt;This role will be in person at our energetic NYC headquarters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base salary for this role will range from $160,000 - $180,000 per year, commensurate with experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end design of key touchpoints in our consumer search and discovery experience — from homepage to search results to property and product pages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with product and engineering to define problems, align on priorities, and ship work that moves real metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run your own lightweight user research — recruit participants, conduct interviews, synthesize findings, and use them to inform design decisions and advocate for the right problems to solve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring a high bar for visual craft to everything you ship — from typography and hierarchy to motion and detail, you&#39;ll help define what &#39;premium&#39; looks and feels like at ResortPass&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive how we bring a refreshed brand to life across the product, elevating the visual and experiential quality of ResortPass&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help evolve our design system and ensure consistency and accessibility across platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help shape the culture and process of a growing design team — your fingerprints will be on how we work, not just what we ship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
